
[1]penitential

   PENITEN'TIAL, a. Proceeding from or expressing penitence or contrition
   of heart; as penitential sorrow or tears.

   PENITEN'TIAL, n. Among the Romanists, a book containing the rules which
   relate to penance and the reconciliation of penitents.
